Note: Active interleukin-10 inhibits the synthesis of a number of cytokines, including IFN-gamma, IL-2, IL-3, TNF and GM-CSF produced by activated macrophages and by helper T cells. Structurally, IL-10 is a protein of about 160 amino acids that contains four conserved cysteines involved in disulfide bonds.

definition.value: Category=family. Note: These receptors may bind neuropeptides and may regulate nociceptor function and/or development, including the sensation or modulation of pain. Because genes for these receptors have undergone duplication, including lineage-specific expansions and pseudogenization, it is sometimes difficult to distinguish orthologs and paralogs.
